Shengwang Temple in Bishan\n\nKaizhang Shengwang Temple located at the peak of Bishan (Mt. Bi), Neihu (also known as Bishanyan, where “yan” refers to “temple” in Minnan) is the biggest Sacred King temple in Taiwan. Frequently attended by worshipers, the temple enshrines the Sacred King-Developer of Zhangzhou Chen Yuan-Guan who reclaimed Fujian and Zhangzhou at the end of Tang dynasty and is considered as the guardian of Zhangzhou. \n\nApart from numerous worshipers, the observatory in front of the Temple is a must-visit place for visitors who wish to have a bird’s eye view over the entire Taipei City. From the platform, you will have a 180° panoramic view of Taipei from the west to the east and from Nankang District to Zhongzheng District. Together with the meandering Keelung River at the foot of the mountain and mountains afar, it presents you a moving scenery of cityscape. Not to mention the neon cityscape of the Greater Taipei at night: the skyscrapers in Xinyi District, Nankang Software Park, Shin Kong Life Insurance Building, Taipei Songshan Airport and so on. Whether the visitors are hikers who take a rest or couple in love dating at sunset, the Temple that erectly stands on the peak of Bishan witnesses the historical trajectory of the development of peak of Bishan (Mt. Bi), Neihu (also known as Bishanyan, where “yan” refers to “temple” in Minnan) is the biggest Sacred King temple in Taiwan. Frequently attended by worshipers, the temple enshrines the Sacred King-Developer of Zhangzhou Chen Yuan-Guan who reclaimed Fujian and Zhangzhou at the end of Tang dynasty and is considered as the guardian of Zhangzhou. \n\nApart from numerous worshipers, the observatory in front of the Temple is a must-visit place for visitors who wish to have a bird’s eye view over the entire Taipei City. From the platform, you will have a 180° panoramic view of Taipei from the west to the east and from Nankang District to Zhongzheng District. Together with the meandering Keelung River at the foot of the mountain and mountains afar, it presents you a moving scenery of cityscape. Not to mention the neon cityscape of the Greater Taipei at night: the skyscrapers in Xinyi District, Nankang Software Park, Shin Kong Life Insurance Building, Taipei Songshan Airport and so on. Whether the visitors are hikers who take a rest or couple in love dating at sunset, the Temple that erectly stands on the peak of Bishan witnesses the historical trajectory of the development of Taipei City.\n-\nSpecial thanks to “Bishanyan Kaizhang Shengwang Temple” and “Taipei Yanping Koxinga Temple” for providing a venue for the installation of camera and wireless network
